    <text id="F3514T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McClendenin, the attending physician, reports on Thomas G. Pilkington's wounded
                    leg.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Emory Hospital
                    <name type="recipient">R. O. Abbott<lb/> Medical Director</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-01-13">January 13, 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Emory Hospital</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>The communication in reference to Thos. G. Pilkington Co. D 126th Pa. Vols. is
                    received; in reply I have the honor to report that said Pilkington was badly
                    wounded in the right thigh, at lower third, at the battle of Fredericksburg.</p>

                <p>The limb is now in an Erysipelatous condition, and it would be folly to discharge
                    the man as I believe his recovery doubtful.</p>

                <p> he is taking <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> every three hours, with two tablespoonfuls of
                    brandy. His diet consists of Essence of Beef, &amp; chicken soup &amp;c.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I have the honor to be your obedient servant</salute>
                    <signed>McClendenin<lb/> Surg. in charge</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
